        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 8:14PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 814 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alpine, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alpine, Alpine-Casparis Municipal Airport, and Elephant Mountain
Wildlife Management Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
